cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a novel autoencoder variant for unsupervised novelty detection on image data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper utilizes GAN and discriminative layers, which are commonly used in the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
